168
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:35,599
Let me guess.

169
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,159
You're an only son.

170
00:08:38,159 --> 00:08:38,840
Oh my god!

171
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:40,520
My intuition tells me you're an only son, right?

172
00:08:40,679 --> 00:08:41,479
That's amazing!

173
00:08:41,719 --> 00:08:42,440
High five!

174
00:08:43,280 --> 00:08:44,640
Stop messing around!

175
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:45,760
You're an only daughter.

176
00:08:46,039 --> 00:08:46,880
I have two older sisters.

177
00:08:47,119 --> 00:08:47,840
Then your two sisters

178
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:48,479
must be just like you,

179
00:08:48,479 --> 00:08:49,280
total tomboys.

180
00:08:49,599 --> 00:08:50,559
Who are you calling a tomboy?

181
00:08:50,599 --> 00:08:51,679
Who are you calling a tomboy?

182
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:52,919
Who are you calling that?

183
00:08:53,479 --> 00:08:54,039
That's enough!

184
00:08:54,960 --> 00:08:55,719
If it weren't for the fact

185
00:08:55,719 --> 00:08:57,119
that you're good friends with our Jiaqi,

186
00:08:57,440 --> 00:08:58,400
I would've kicked you out long ago.

187
00:08:58,840 --> 00:09:00,000
"Your Jiaqi"?

188
00:09:02,119 --> 00:09:03,760
Don't tell me you like Lin Jiaqi?

189
00:09:04,159 --> 00:09:04,880
What's it to you?

190
00:09:05,239 --> 00:09:05,719
You...

191
00:09:06,359 --> 00:09:07,719
How can you like Lin Jiaqi?

192
00:09:08,239 --> 00:09:09,679
How can you like Lin Jiaqi?

193
00:09:09,679 --> 00:09:10,239
Tomboy!

194
00:09:10,599 --> 00:09:11,280
Don't move, tomboy!

195
00:09:11,280 --> 00:09:12,200
Who are you calling a tomboy?

196
00:09:12,359 --> 00:09:13,280
Who are you calling a tomboy?

197
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:14,000
Who are you calling that?

198
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:14,679
If you hit me again...

199
00:09:14,679 --> 00:09:15,679
Hitting me again is crossing the line!

200
00:09:15,679 --> 00:09:16,359
You're crossing the line!

201
00:09:16,359 --> 00:09:17,080
Let go!

202
00:09:17,479 --> 00:09:17,919
You...

203
00:09:18,280 --> 00:09:18,599
If you hit me again...

204
00:09:18,599 --> 00:09:19,039
Let go!

205
00:09:19,039 --> 00:09:19,520
If you hit me again...

206
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:23,520
A watch.

207
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:30,880
There's a...

208
00:09:31,039 --> 00:09:32,520
A watch with a strange pattern.

209
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:35,479
The person wearing that watch

210
00:09:35,799 --> 00:09:36,599
is connected to this murder.

211
00:09:37,479 --> 00:09:38,039
What?

212
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:38,880
What pattern?

213
00:09:42,559 --> 00:09:44,159
Anyway, the pattern on this watch is...

214
00:09:44,679 --> 00:09:45,760
related to tropical fish.

215
00:09:52,799 --> 00:09:53,520
If we can't find

216
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:55,000
a supplier for the vanilla raw materials,

217
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:56,520
should we just go directly to the farms?

218
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:58,000
Go directly to the farms?

219
00:09:59,880 --> 00:10:01,520
I took a look at the

220
00:10:01,520 --> 00:10:02,479
project development plan from Chairman Gu's time.

221
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:04,880
Originally, our company was also planning

222
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:07,080
to develop some high-priced eco-friendly products.

223
00:10:07,479 --> 00:10:09,080
Near the Tongzhou Factory, there is a

224
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:10,559
150-mu vanilla field.

225
00:10:10,880 --> 00:10:11,760
We were supposed to sign a contract,

226
00:10:11,760 --> 00:10:13,119
but I don't know why it didn't go through.

227
00:10:13,440 --> 00:10:13,919
This

228
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,520
is the project development plan drafted at the time.

229
00:10:16,039 --> 00:10:17,400
If we go directly to the farms,

230
00:10:18,719 --> 00:10:19,880
then we'll need to do

231
00:10:20,119 --> 00:10:21,200
