274
00:11:59,280 --> 00:12:00,479
If you don't, I have things to do.

275
00:12:00,679 --> 00:12:01,679
I have to go.

276
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:03,400
No, no, I do, I do.

277
00:12:03,640 --> 00:12:05,119
Why else would I come all the way here?

278
00:12:05,559 --> 00:12:06,640
Come, sit, sit.

279
00:12:06,719 --> 00:12:07,080
Sit.

280
00:12:07,280 --> 00:12:08,159
Come on, come here.

281
00:12:08,679 --> 00:12:09,280
Come, sit.

282
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:10,599
I really have something to say.

283
00:12:10,719 --> 00:12:11,400
I really do.

284
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:12,119
Just sit down first.

285
00:12:12,840 --> 00:12:13,359
Right.

286
00:12:13,840 --> 00:12:15,080
Mr. Gu asked me to tell you.

287
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:17,479
The person wearing the tropical fish watch

288
00:12:17,559 --> 00:12:19,119
was at the crime scene.

289
00:12:26,039 --> 00:12:27,840
Did Gu Tiancheng dream this up again?

290
00:12:28,320 --> 00:12:29,000
Why do we have nothing better to do

291
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:30,159
than listen to his sleep talking?

292
00:12:40,119 --> 00:12:40,880
What are you doing?

293
00:12:41,919 --> 00:12:43,239
The sleeves are too long.

294
00:12:44,159 --> 00:12:44,840
Are they?

295
00:12:45,440 --> 00:12:46,799
They're supposed to be this long.

296
00:12:47,320 --> 00:12:48,159
Country bumpkin.

297
00:12:49,599 --> 00:12:51,039
You're so unromantic.

298
00:12:52,599 --> 00:12:53,559
What are you saying?

299
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:55,280
A grown man talking

300
00:12:55,359 --> 00:12:56,760
like a buzzing mosquito.

301
00:12:57,359 --> 00:12:57,840
Right.

302
00:12:58,719 --> 00:12:59,559
Who's like you?

303
00:12:59,679 --> 00:13:00,080
Right?

304
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:00,919
Moving like a fleeing hare,

305
00:13:01,520 --> 00:13:02,679
speaking with a booming voice.

306
00:13:02,760 --> 00:13:03,760
Get out of here.

307
00:13:04,760 --> 00:13:05,400
Hurry, hurry.

308
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:06,520
Alright, stop messing around.

309
00:13:06,919 --> 00:13:08,520
Gu Tiancheng just sent you to deliver this?

310
00:13:09,799 --> 00:13:10,119
Yes.

311
00:13:10,479 --> 00:13:11,159
Nothing else?

312
00:13:12,280 --> 00:13:13,119
If there's anything else,

313
00:13:13,919 --> 00:13:14,960
I'll come find you again.

314
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:16,359
Alright, I'm not chatting with you anymore.

315
00:13:16,799 --> 00:13:17,599
I'm in a hurry to get back to the station.

316
00:13:18,080 --> 00:13:18,840
I'm leaving.

317
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:19,679
I'll take this.

318
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:20,400
Wait.

319
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:28,640
It will succeed.

320
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:39,840
You must be tired after running around all day.

321
00:13:40,280 --> 00:13:41,599
Get some rest early when we get back.

322
00:13:42,840 --> 00:13:43,960
You have the nerve to say that.

323
00:13:45,359 --> 00:13:46,320
I wonder who it was

324
00:13:46,679 --> 00:13:48,239
sleeping like a piglet in the car.

325
00:13:48,599 --> 00:13:49,960
Your drool almost got on me.

326
00:13:50,679 --> 00:13:52,119
Making me drive the whole way.

327
00:13:53,760 --> 00:13:55,119
Are you the secretary or am I?

328
00:13:55,119 --> 00:13:56,520
It wasn't as exaggerated as you say.

329
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:00,359
What's wrong?

330
00:14:00,719 --> 00:14:01,440
Your nose is bleeding.

331
00:14:01,520 --> 00:14:02,119
You have a nosebleed.

332
00:14:02,599 --> 00:14:03,359
Come here first.

333
00:14:03,960 --> 00:14:04,640
Don't move, don't move.

334
00:14:08,840 --> 00:14:10,359
Why the sudden nosebleed?

335
00:14:11,880 --> 00:14:12,799
Don't move, let me see.

336
00:14:13,599 --> 00:14:14,440
It's coming out.

337
00:14:18,840 --> 00:14:19,719
Rather than looking pitiful,

338
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:21,440
I think you look funny right now.

339
00:14:22,280 --> 00:14:23,119
Who looks funny?

340
00:14:23,599 --> 00:14:24,159
You do.

341
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:25,640
I don't want this.

342
00:14:25,640 --> 00:14:26,119
What's wrong?

343
00:14:26,119 --> 00:14:26,919
It's too ugly.

344
00:14:39,919 --> 00:14:40,760
Didn't we have an appointment?

345
00:14:41,239 --> 00:14:41,960
Why is no one here?

346
00:14:42,359 --> 00:14:42,960
Yeah.

347
00:14:43,919 --> 00:14:44,760
Let's go in and take a look.

348
00:14:47,799 --> 00:14:48,919
This is our search warrant.

349
00:14:53,799 --> 00:14:54,599
Come take a picture of this.

350
00:14:55,599 --> 00:14:56,400
What happened?

351
00:14:58,840 --> 00:14:59,440
Mr. Gu.

352
00:15:00,640 --> 00:15:01,599
You came at the right time.

353
00:15:02,119 --> 00:15:04,080
We clearly got the quarantine report long ago.

354
00:15:04,159 --> 00:15:05,760
But someone is playing tricks behind our backs.

355
00:15:06,119 --> 00:15:06,719
Saying that

356
00:15:07,119 --> 00:15:08,039
our agricultural products

357
00:15:08,320 --> 00:15:10,119
have detectable pesticide residue.

358
00:15:10,280 --> 00:15:11,760
If this rumor spreads,

359
00:15:12,119 --> 00:15:13,320
our farm will be ruined.

360
00:15:13,359 --> 00:15:14,799
What about the delivery we agreed on yesterday?

361
00:15:15,119 --> 00:15:16,559
Before the issue is resolved,

362
00:15:16,960 --> 00:15:18,200
I'm afraid we can't deliver the goods.

363
00:15:18,640 --> 00:15:19,520
I'm sorry.

364
00:15:36,799 --> 00:15:37,559
Mr. Gu.

365
00:15:38,559 --> 00:15:40,479
You don't look so good today.

366
00:15:41,320 --> 00:15:42,400
Didn't sleep well last night?

367
00:15:50,960 --> 00:15:51,799
Does it have to be this way?

368
00:15:53,239 --> 00:15:54,000
What way?

369
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:56,320
I'm just showing some concern for you.

370
00:15:56,640 --> 00:15:57,760
I know you did it.

371
00:15:58,119 --> 00:15:59,039
I don't understand.

372
00:15:59,039 --> 00:15:59,840
What are you talking about?

373
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:01,000
It's fine if you come after me,

374
00:16:02,320 --> 00:16:03,840
but what did the people at the farm do to you?

375
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:08,039
Even if I did it,

376
00:16:08,919 --> 00:16:09,919
do you know what?

377
00:16:11,760 --> 00:16:12,919
You're the one who's more at fault.

378
00:16:14,080 --> 00:16:15,359
If you had given up earlier,

379
00:16:15,679 --> 00:16:17,200
none of this would be happening.

380
00:16:17,880 --> 00:16:19,719
And you wouldn't have dragged so many people down with you.

381
00:16:20,719 --> 00:16:21,520
Besides,

382
00:16:21,880 --> 00:16:23,520
this is just the beginning.

383
00:16:24,280 --> 00:16:26,200
From now on, everyone who stands with you

384
00:16:26,200 --> 00:16:27,559
will suffer because of you,

385
00:16:28,719 --> 00:16:29,960
all because they are helping you.

386
00:16:37,359 --> 00:16:38,039
What are you doing?

387
00:16:38,760 --> 00:16:39,719
I was just thinking that I used to be

388
00:16:39,719 --> 00:16:41,599
exactly like you are right now.

389
00:16:42,840 --> 00:16:43,719
What do you mean?

390
00:16:44,599 --> 00:16:46,159
Feng Ziang, do you know why Lin Jiaqi

391
00:16:46,159 --> 00:16:47,039
won't go to your side?

392
00:16:47,039 --> 00:16:47,640
Shut up!

393
00:16:54,799 --> 00:16:56,159
Feng Ziang, do you know why Lin Jiaqi

394
00:16:56,159 --> 00:16:57,239
won't go to your side?

395
00:16:57,559 --> 00:16:58,679
Because of Lin Jiaqi, I went

396
00:16:59,520 --> 00:17:00,559
from being a monster

397
00:17:01,479 --> 00:17:02,640
to the person I am today.

398
00:17:03,359 --> 00:17:04,760
But because of Lin Jiaqi, you

399
00:17:05,959 --> 00:17:07,359
are turning into a monster.

400
00:17:08,119 --> 00:17:08,959
No woman

401
00:17:08,959 --> 00:17:10,359
would ever want to follow a monster.

402
00:17:27,520 --> 00:17:28,199
How's it going?

403
00:17:29,680 --> 00:17:30,920
Nothing special, really.

404
00:17:32,040 --> 00:17:33,239
So there's no progress.

405
00:17:34,280 --> 00:17:35,160
As for progress...

406
00:17:35,239 --> 00:17:36,119
There is one thing.

407
00:17:36,319 --> 00:17:38,160
Gu Tiancheng recently accessed

408
00:17:38,160 --> 00:17:39,479
someone else's medical records without permission.

409
00:17:39,920 --> 00:17:40,839
Medical records?

410
00:17:41,719 --> 00:17:43,479
The heart donor's medical records.

411
00:17:43,839 --> 00:17:44,839
To be exact,

412
00:17:44,839 --> 00:17:46,439
it was done by his subordinate.

413
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:47,880
That guy named...

414
00:17:48,520 --> 00:17:49,520
Qi Shuai.

415
00:17:49,719 --> 00:17:50,959
Are they involved in

416
00:17:51,239 --> 00:17:52,280
human organ trafficking?

417
00:17:52,839 --> 00:17:53,640
Not exactly.

418
00:17:54,079 --> 00:17:56,079
But what I find strange is

419
00:17:56,479 --> 00:17:58,239
that Gu Tiancheng also went to see

420
00:17:58,439 --> 00:17:59,760
the donor's family.

421
00:17:59,760 --> 00:18:01,839
Nowadays, organ donors and recipients meeting

422
00:18:01,839 --> 00:18:02,560
isn't illegal.

423
00:18:03,760 --> 00:18:04,280
But

424
00:18:04,680 --> 00:18:06,439
accessing someone else's

425
00:18:06,439 --> 00:18:07,479
medical records without permission

426
00:18:07,479 --> 00:18:08,560
does count as illegal.

427
00:18:08,959 --> 00:18:10,319
At most, he'll be called to the station for questioning.

428
00:18:12,239 --> 00:18:13,079
Forget it, you can go.

429
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:14,800
I'll find you if I need anything.

430
00:18:20,280 --> 00:18:21,000
Have some water.

431
00:18:21,800 --> 00:18:22,439
Thanks.

432
00:18:25,079 --> 00:18:26,640
Even small businesses out of town won't work?

433
00:18:32,199 --> 00:18:34,160
None of them can supply in large quantities.

434
00:18:36,280 --> 00:18:37,319
Then what should we do?

435
00:18:37,520 --> 00:18:39,520
The deadline to repay the funds is approaching.

436
00:18:47,319 --> 00:18:48,000
All right.

437
00:18:48,640 --> 00:18:49,319
Look at you.

438
00:18:50,079 --> 00:18:51,160
You're frowning.

439
00:18:56,599 --> 00:18:58,119
Although there are many difficulties right now,

440
00:18:59,280 --> 00:19:00,119
I believe

441
00:19:00,359 --> 00:19:01,520
there's always a way out.

442
00:19:03,319 --> 00:19:05,079
So cheer up.

443
00:19:05,640 --> 00:19:06,920
Tomorrow will definitely be better.

444
00:19:11,479 --> 00:19:12,479
Why do you have to pretend

445
00:19:12,599 --> 00:19:14,239
like nothing is wrong?

446
00:19:16,280 --> 00:19:18,319
If you're tired, don't force yourself.

447
00:19:18,760 --> 00:19:19,880
What if your health breaks down?

448
00:19:21,719 --> 00:19:23,000
I remember you told me

449
00:19:23,479 --> 00:19:24,719
that if I felt it was too hard,

450
00:19:25,040 --> 00:19:25,959
I could rely on you.

451
00:19:26,839 --> 00:19:28,160
But now it's your turn.

452
00:19:29,040 --> 00:19:30,319
Why do you have to carry it all by yourself?

453
00:19:35,239 --> 00:19:36,680
Actually, I feel like lately

454
00:19:37,319 --> 00:19:38,359
you seem quite lonely.

455
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:40,880
It makes me

456
00:19:41,560 --> 00:19:42,640
feel sorry for you.

457
00:19:44,680 --> 00:19:46,239
And I don't know how to help you.

458
00:19:52,599 --> 00:19:53,880
Hearing you say it like that,

459
00:19:54,920 --> 00:19:56,439
even I feel sorry for myself.

460
00:20:00,800 --> 00:20:02,599
What you just said to me,

461
00:20:03,920 --> 00:20:05,199
can I interpret it as

462
00:20:06,719 --> 00:20:07,839
you liking me a little?

463
00:20:09,239 --> 00:20:10,119
I have things to do.

464
00:20:10,119 --> 00:20:10,800
I'll get going.
